# Project conventions for rag-assistant

## Stack
- Python 3.11+, type hints required on public functions.
- FastAPI for HTTP, psycopg 3 (sync) for DB, openai 1.x async client.
- pgvector + HNSW index, cosine distance.
- sentence-transformers for embeddings + reranker.
- pytest with `asyncio_mode = "auto"`, ruff for lint.

## Style
- `from __future__ import annotations` at the top of every module.
- Public functions have a short docstring explaining *why*, not *what*.
- No bare `except:`; catch the narrowest exception that makes sense.
- Prefer dependency injection (Protocols) over module-level globals so tests
  can swap in fakes without monkeypatching internals.
- SQL lives in inline strings, parameterised — never f-string interpolation.

## Tests
- Unit tests must NOT require torch / sentence-transformers / a live Postgres.
  Use `FakeEmbedder`, `FakeReranker`, mocked `psycopg` connection, mocked
  `AsyncOpenAI`.
- One assertion concept per test, descriptive `test_*` names.
- New features need at least one happy-path test and one failure-mode test.

## Don't
- Don't add new dependencies without updating `requirements.txt` / `requirements-ml.txt`.
- Don't put heavy model loads at import time — use `@lru_cache` on a getter.
- Don't bypass `pydantic-settings`; all config goes through `src/config.py`.
